You are working on Eterapp — a Bulgarian AI emotional support SaaS.

## Stack
- Vite + React + TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS (utility classes only, no custom CSS)
- Framer Motion (already installed)
- Supabase (auth + database)
- Netlify (hosting + serverless functions in netlify/functions/)
- i18next (BG primary, EN secondary — all strings via t() keys)
- shadcn/ui components in src/components/ui/

## Critical rules

### Before writing any code
1. Check if the component/function you want to import actually exists and is exported
2. Check src/components/ui/ before importing UI components
3. Never import something you haven't verified exists

### TypeScript
- Strict mode is ON — no `any` unless absolutely necessary
- Always cast types explicitly (e.g. Number(), String())
- Props must match component type definitions exactly
- Check variant unions before using variant="something"

### Supabase
- chat_sessions.id is BIGINT — all foreign keys must be BIGINT not UUID
- Netlify functions use SUPABASE_URL and SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY (no VITE_ prefix)
- Frontend uses VITE_SUPABASE_URL and VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY

### Netlify functions
- All functions in netlify/functions/*.ts
- Always validate auth token at the top
- Always return { statusCode, body: JSON.stringify({}) }
- Use try/catch with proper error responses

### i18n
- Every user-visible string MUST use t("key")
- Add keys to BOTH bg and en sections in src/lib/i18n.ts
- Never hardcode Bulgarian or English text directly in JSX

### File structure
- Pages: src/pages/
- Components: src/components/
- UI primitives: src/components/ui/ (shadcn — do not modify unless necessary)
- Hooks: src/hooks/
- DB client: src/lib/supabaseClient.ts

